# Voxtype / Whisper biasing dictionary — EXAMPLE.
#
# On a fresh clone, copy this to `dictionary.txt` and make it yours:
#
#   cp voxtype/dictionary.txt.example voxtype/dictionary.txt
#
# `dictionary.txt` is gitignored, so your personal edits stay private and are
# never pushed. This `.example` is the only tracked copy.
#
# One term per line. Blank lines and lines starting with `#` are ignored.
# At daemon launch the `voxtype-with-dictionary.sh` wrapper flattens this into a single
# `Dictionary: a, b, c, ...` string and passes it to `voxtype --initial-prompt`,
# hinting Whisper at proper nouns it would otherwise mistranscribe. Edit the
# file, then restart the daemon:
#
#   systemctl --user restart voxtype.service
#
# Keep terms as you want them spelled in the output (capitalisation matters).

# --- People (add your own — names, handles) ---
# John Doe
# Bob

# --- Orgs / places / education (add your own) ---
# Acme Corp
# State University

